Preheat your #oven{} to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced). Halve the @bell pepper{2} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{3} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Pour the @water{300%ml} for the rice into a #medium saucepan{} with a tight-fitting lid.

Stir in the @basmati rice{150%g} and @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to the boil. Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Pop the peppers onto a #large baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{1%tbsp}(for roasting), season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until soft and slightly charred, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Drain the @king prawns{300%g} and pat dry with #kitchen paper{}. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw prawns.

While everything cooks, heat the @olive oil{1%tbsp}(for the sauce) in a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the onion and season with salt and pepper. Fry until soft and sweet, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Stir in the @chilli flakes{1%tsp} and garlic. Cook for ~{2-3%minutes}.

> Add less chilli flakes if you'd prefer things milder.

Add the @red wine vinegar{12%ml} and allow it to bubble away until evaporated, ~{1%minute}.

Stir the @tomato puree{30%g} into the pan and cook for ~{1%minute}, then pour in the @water{100%ml}(for the sauce) and bring to the boil. Season with salt and pepper.

Stir in the prawns, @sugar{1/4%tsp} for the sauce and @vegetable stock paste{10%g}.

Cook until the sauce has thickened and the prawns are cooked, ~{5-6%minutes}. Remove from the heat. IMPORTANT: The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

Taste your sauce and add salt and pepper if needed. Stir through the roasted peppers, adding a splash of water if it's a little too thick.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and share between your #bowls{}. Top with the prawns, spooning over all of the sauce from the pan.

Enjoy!